Vanilla, caramel, flowers. Damn good. Drinks easy for 120 proof.
89-2T @ 59.9%
Pretty smooth, more backend bite than I'm used to with 4 Rose's in general.  Keep in mind it's a private barrel so the proof may vary.  Prefer the OESQ

Great vanilla nose slight caramel 
Fruity taste vanilla end
Absolutely amazing! Mild spice, cinnamon,  nutmeg, vanilla,  rich, butterscotch,  maple syrup,
Creamy and fruity on the nose and upfront on the taste with a smooth finish. Great one!
Burnt brown sugar, caramel, rich but mildly, smooth spice of nutmeg, hot but enticing
Magnum’s select - a lot of complexity to this one. Very tasty. Caramel tones.
This is an amazing pour. Smooth on the front end and a cherry bomb finish.

sweet on the palette, flavor lasts for a good amount of time, high viscosity

nose is strong floral with a hint of oak, lots of vanilla

Palette starts sweet (heavy vanilla) and moves to slight spice, but that’s to be expected with the proof- spice doesn’t overpower the pour
